Sentence: Who called the manager yesterday?
who : interrogative pronoun, subject of the verb "called"
called : verb "call", past tense, active voice
the : definite article, singular
manager : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "called"
yesterday : adverb of time, adjunct indicating when the action occurred

Sentence: What did you buy at the store?
what : interrogative pronoun, direct object of the verb "buy"
did : auxiliary verb "do", past tense, used for question formation
you : personal pronoun, second person singular or plural, subject of the verb "buy"
buy : main verb "buy", base form
at : preposition introducing the location
the : definite article, singular
store : common noun, singular, object of the preposition "at"

Sentence: Where are they going for their vacation?
where : interrogative adverb, adjunct indicating location
are : auxiliary verb "be", present tense, third person plural
they : personal pronoun, third person plural, subject of the verb "going"
going : main verb "go", present participle
for : preposition indicating purpose
their : possessive determiner, third person plural
vacation : common noun, singular, object of the preposition "for"

Sentence: When will the train arrive at the station?
when : interrogative adverb, adjunct indicating time
will : auxiliary verb, future tense marker
the : definite article, singular
train : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "arrive"
arrive : main verb "arrive", base form
at : preposition introducing the location
the : definite article, singular
station : common noun, singular, object of the preposition "at"

Sentence: Why did she cancel the meeting?
why : interrogative adverb, adjunct indicating reason
did : auxiliary verb "do", past tense, used for question formation
she : personal pronoun, third person singular feminine, subject of the verb "cancel"
cancel : main verb "cancel", base form
the : definite article, singular
meeting : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "cancel"

Sentence: How does this machine work?
how : interrogative adverb, adjunct indicating manner
does : auxiliary verb "do", present tense, third person singular
this : demonstrative determiner, singular
machine : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "work"
work : main verb "work", base form

Sentence: Which book belongs to Sarah?
which : interrogative determiner, modifying the noun "book"
book : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "belongs"
belongs : verb "belong", present tense, third person singular
to : preposition indicating possession
Sarah : proper noun, singular, object of the preposition "to"

Sentence: Whose keys are on the table?
whose : interrogative possessive determiner, modifying the noun "keys"
keys : common noun, plural, subject of the verb "are"
are : verb "be", present tense, third person plural
on : preposition indicating location
the : definite article, singular
table : common noun, singular, object of the preposition "on"

Sentence: Who wrote this famous novel?
who : interrogative pronoun, subject of the verb "wrote"
wrote : verb "write", past tense, active voice
this : demonstrative determiner, singular
famous : adjective, modifying the noun "novel"
novel : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "wrote"

Sentence: What caused the power outage last night?
what : interrogative pronoun, subject of the verb "caused"
caused : verb "cause", past tense, active voice
the : definite article, singular
power : common noun, singular, part of the compound noun "power outage"
outage : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "caused"
last : adjective, indicating time
night : common noun, singular, adjunct indicating time

Sentence: Where did you hide the treasure map?
where : interrogative adverb, adjunct indicating location
did : auxiliary verb "do", past tense, used for question formation
you : personal pronoun, second person, subject of the verb "hide"
